@startuml ProbationClassification_SP_GetProbationScan
title CTS_DC_CustClassification_ProbationScan_Get - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam activityBorderColor #4CAF50

start

:Stored Procedure Called;
note right
  **SP Name**: CTS_DC_CustClassification_ProbationScan_Get
  **Database**: CTS_DataCenter.ctsService (MySQL)
  **Timeout**: 300 seconds (5 minutes)
  **Called From**: ProbationScanningGetCriteria
end note

partition "Input Parameters" {
  :Receive @ip_NoOfRecord (int);
  note right
    **Batch Size**: Number of customers to retrieve
    **Typical Value**: 5000-10000
    **Purpose**: Limit result set size
  end note
}

partition "Get Pagination State" {
  :Read System Parameters;
  note right
    **Get Current Position**:
    ```sql
    SELECT Value INTO @LastCustID
    FROM CTS_SystemParameter
    WHERE ParameterKey = 'DailyProbation_LastCustID'
    
    SELECT Value INTO @LastCategoryID
    FROM CTS_SystemParameter
    WHERE ParameterKey = 'DailyProbation_LastCategoryID'
    ```
    
    **Initial State** (first run):
    - @LastCustID = 0
    - @LastCategoryID = 0
    
    **Subsequent Runs**:
    - Start from last processed position
    - Resume processing seamlessly
  end note

  :Set @LastCustID and @LastCategoryID;
}

partition "Query Probation Customers" {
  :SELECT from CTSCustomerClassification;
  note right
    **Query**:
    ```sql
    SELECT 
      CustID,
      SportGroupID
    FROM CTSCustomerClassification
    WHERE 1=1
      AND ProbationEndDate > NOW()  -- Still in probation
      AND CustID > @LastCustID      -- Pagination
    ORDER BY CustID, CategoryID     -- Consistent ordering
    LIMIT @ip_NoOfRecord            -- Batch size
    ```
    
    **Filter Conditions**:
    1. **ProbationEndDate > NOW()**:
       - Customer still in probation period
       - Not yet completed probation
       - Active for re-classification
    
    2. **CustID > @LastCustID**:
       - Pagination condition
       - Skip already processed customers
       - Start from last position + 1
    
    **Ordering**:
    - PRIMARY: CustID (ascending)
    - SECONDARY: CategoryID (ascending)
    - Ensures consistent pagination
    - Prevents skipping or duplicates
    
    **Limit**:
    - Batch size (@ip_NoOfRecord)
    - Memory-efficient processing
    - Balance performance vs throughput
  end note

  :Build Result Set;
  note right
    **Result Columns**:
    - CustId (long): Customer identifier
    - SportGroupId (int): Sport classification
    
    **Usage**:
    - Input to probation re-classification
    - Identifies customers to process
  end note
}

partition "Capture Pagination State" {
  if (Result set has data?) then (yes)
    :Get Last CustID from result;
    :Get Last CategoryID from result;
    note right
      **Extract Last Values**:
      ```sql
      SELECT 
        MAX(CustID) INTO @op_LastCustID,
        MAX(CategoryID) INTO @op_LastCategoryID
      FROM ResultSet
      ```
      
      **Purpose**:
      - Track progress for next batch
      - Enable resumable processing
      - Output parameters for caller
    end note
  else (no)
    :Set @op_LastCustID = 0;
    :Set @op_LastCategoryID = 0;
    note right
      **Empty Result**:
      - All probation customers processed
      - Reset pagination state
      - Signal completion
    end note
  endif

  :Set Output Parameters;
  note right
    **Output Parameters**:
    - @op_LastCustID (long)
    - @op_LastCategoryID (int)
    
    **These values will be**:
    - Stored in system parameters
    - Used in next iteration/job run
    - Enable pagination across runs
  end note
}

partition "Return Results" {
  :Return ProbationEntity[];
  note right
    **Return Type**: List<ProbationEntity>
    
    **Entity Structure**:
    - CustId (long)
    - SportGroupId (int)
    
    **Count**: 0 to @ip_NoOfRecord
    
    **Empty Result Indicates**:
    - All probation customers processed
    - Job can complete
  end note
}

:Log Execution;
note right
  **Logging**:
  - Customer count returned
  - LastCustID position
  - LastCategoryID position
  - Query execution time
  - Any errors/warnings
end note

if (Result count = 0?) then (yes)
  :Signal completion;
  note right
    **No more probation customers**:
    - All processed
    - Job will exit do-while loop
    - Success completion
  end note
else (no)
  :More customers to process;
  note right
    **Continue processing**:
    - Returned customers will be re-classified
    - Next iteration will fetch more
    - Loop continues
  end note
endif

note right
  **Pagination Logic**:
  
  **First Iteration**:
  - @LastCustID = 0
  - @LastCategoryID = 0
  - Get first batch (TOP @ip_NoOfRecord)
  - Return @op_LastCustID = MAX(CustID) from result
  
  **Subsequent Iterations**:
  - @LastCustID = @op_LastCustID (from previous)
  - @LastCategoryID = @op_LastCategoryID (from previous)
  - Get next batch (CustID > @LastCustID)
  - Return new @op_LastCustID
  
  **Last Iteration**:
  - Returns < @ip_NoOfRecord customers (partial batch)
  - Or returns 0 customers (all done)
  - @op_LastCustID set accordingly
  
  **Advantages**:
  1. **Resumable**: Can resume after interruption
  2. **No Duplicates**: CustID > @LastCustID prevents re-processing
  3. **Memory Efficient**: Batch processing
  4. **Consistent**: ORDER BY ensures reliable pagination
  5. **Persistent**: System parameters survive restarts
  
  **Index Requirements**:
  ```sql
  CREATE INDEX IX_Probation_Scan 
  ON CTSCustomerClassification (ProbationEndDate, CustID, CategoryID)
  ```
  - Fast filtering on ProbationEndDate
  - Efficient pagination on CustID
  - Secondary ordering on CategoryID
  
  **Probation Period Check**:
  - ProbationEndDate > NOW(): Still in probation
  - ProbationEndDate <= NOW(): Probation completed
  - ProbationEndDate IS NULL: No probation
  
  **Typical Batch Sizes**:
  - Small: 1000 (conservative, slower)
  - Medium: 5000 (balanced)
  - Large: 10000 (aggressive, faster but more memory)
  
  **Performance**:
  - Query time: < 1 second (with proper indexes)
  - Total job time: Depends on probation customer count
  - Example: 50,000 customers ÷ 5,000 batch = 10 iterations
end note

stop

@enduml

